column1: KEEP YOUR PROGRAM BACKED UP AT ALL TIMES
1. Never use this file (blankpower.xls): Keep as a Master Copy.
Go to File: Save As: Choose a name for your working copy.
2. wilks, men, women, calc: These work sheets are hidden, and do not, need to be altered:
3. Do not change any rows or columns in any work sheets except row E1& row E2 in VIEW sheet
These two rows alter venue and date to suit your competition e.g. South Yorkshires 25/12/00
If you use cut copy and paste the formulas may be deleted and would result in faulty work sheet
To move a row use cut and insert
4. M or F, class,name,club, class,rack,and age are in a drop down lists, to save typing.
5 All Data required for view sheet must be entered in the data sheet.
To add any NAME to the Mdata or Wdata go to work sheet add name + weight class at the end of the list
To add to clubs, go to the data sheet, Input club name at the end of list
The data will go to the correct place via V.B.A. code.
5. Curser Direction: To alter the way the curser goes to the next cell after the enter key is pressed:
Go to Tools, Options, Edit, Direction: Handy for entering data in your preferred direction.
6. All class sections are auto sorted. So beware to type correct totals to names
7. Failed Attempt: click ctrl+n. Mistakes can be reversed by clicking ctrl+g.
8. The sheets are set up for 80 competitors. For any more you will have to copy and paste the formulas.
9. To Print Out the results go to View then custom views;
Detail uses 2 sheets Landscape to prints out all results including any record attempts and positions,
Summary prints out totals for groups and overall positions on a single portrait sheet
10. To sort Individual groups Highlight Sort by sub total col P or Total col U
Any problems contact Alan Twigg at the address below.
